FAQ















FAQ






How to Update your Ember
1. Download and launch the Ember app.
Note: the Ember App is required to pair and update the Ember Mug, it cannot be paired through your smartphones bluetooth settings.

2. Once your Ember is paired (having tro...


How long does it take to charge Ember?
It takes approximately 2 hours to charge your Ember Mug.


What is the temperature range?
The ember mug provides the precision temperature control between 120°F and 145°F, covering the full range of preferred hot beverage drinking temperatures.


Is Ember dishwasher safe?
We do not not recommend putting your Ember in the dishwasher. We have found that using a dish brush is the best tool for getting to those hard to reach places.

The lid is dishwasher safe.


Can I use my Ember without pairing to a phone?
Yes! Your Ember can be used completely independent of the phone by rotating the dial on the bottom of the mug to select your temperature. Using it independently will limit you from customizing specific features...


What is the rapid-cooling technology?
Ember has the ability to rapidly cool to the perfect temperature you choose. The patented phase change cooling system allows scorching hot liquids to cool at a faster rate to your desired temperature.


Does Ember work for cold drinks too?
The Ember mug will not actively refrigerate a cold beverage for long periods. It will keep the contents cold like any other thermos would, but Ember was specifically designed to rapidly cool scolding hot liquid...


Can the mug switch between Fahrenheit and Celsius?
Yes. You can switch between Fahrenheit and Celsius using the settings icon on the Ember App.


What type of battery does my Ember use?
The Ember uses a standard lithium ion battery, specifically designed for providing the best energy efficiency for an amazing user experience.


Is there a car charger?
Unfortunately not yet. We have definitely plans to launch a car charger compatible for your Ember. While we want you to have the best experience with Ember and its potential to charge on the go, we do not have ...







